text: - [Narrator] What does 10 years
of strategic collaboration look like?
Let's find out from AWS and Splunk.

In 2012, AWS launched
the AWS Partner Network,
and Splunk joined that same year.
Fast forward to today,
where innovative AWS and Splunk services

are accelerating cloud
migration and modernization

with full-stack visibility,
real-time monitoring,
and AI-driven analytics.
When you're migrating to the cloud,
Splunk's solutions compliment AWS services
to deliver end-to-end visibility.
Use operations and service insights

to ensure effective
migration and modernization.

Does your app delivery
to time need a boost?
Observability from Splunk makes it easier

to troubleshoot containers,
microservices, and pipelines
so you can deploy apps faster.
Need to know the performance
of each part of your technology stack?

Observability from Splunk
can handle that too,

with a complete view of your
AWS environment and services.

And, AWS and Splunk
Security services protect

your environments with
detection, investigation,

response, auditing, and
compliance capabilities.
If you want better visibility and control
while delivering apps faster,
AWS and Splunk are here to help.

For 10 years, we have
been better together,
and we're just getting started.
(light music)
